Title : Leesville, Indiana
Text : '''Leesville''' is an [[Unincorporated area|unincorporated community]] in [[Lawrence County, Indiana|Lawrence County]], [[Indiana]], [[United States]].<ref>{{GNIS|437744}}</ref>

[[File:Leesville, IN Historic Marker.jpg|thumb|Historic marker for Leesville Indiana, describing its founding and the history of the town.]]

==History==
Leesville was founded in 1818.<ref>{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EVQ0AQAAMAAJ&pg=PA172#v=onepage&q&f=false | title=History of Lawrence, Orange, and Washington Counties, Indiana: From the Earliest Time to the Present | publisher=Higginson Book Company | year=1884 | pages=172}}</ref> A majority of the early settlers being natives of [[Lee County, Virginia]], caused the name to be selected.<ref>{{cite book|title=History of Lawrence and Monroe Counties, Indiana: Their People, Industries, and Institutions|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rVM0AQAAMAAJ&pg=PA36|year=1914|publisher=B.F. Bowen|page=36}}</ref>

